Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.34,0:00:18.32,Lucy-Song-Title,,0,0,0,,[I want to be a rainbow]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.60,0:00:29.78,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa hoshifuru yoru ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.03,0:00:36.71,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono tomoshibi wo keshi wa shinai to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.99,0:00:47.83,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wasurenai wa akane no asa ni chikatta kotoba
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.09,0:00:56.77,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Wakaba ni somaru haru wo yobou to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.05,0:01:08.66,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Ono utsu hibiki michi hiraku utagoe
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.94,0:01:20.55,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kodama ga mune ni hazunde kuru no
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.83,0:01:26.39,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kono oosora no niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.67,0:01:36.19,Lucy-Song-Japanese,,0,0,0,,Kibou ni todoku niji ni naritai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.60,0:00:29.78,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow I made on that starry night
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.03,0:00:36.71,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To not let this flame die
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.99,0:00:47.83,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I won't forget the vow made on that brilliant red morning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.09,0:00:56.77,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,To call out for spring, dyed with young leaves
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.05,0:01:08.66,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,Cutting axes open up roads, under the sound of singing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.94,0:01:20.55,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,The echoes bounce around in my chest
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.83,0:01:26.39,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow in this big sky
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.67,0:01:36.19,Lucy-Song-English,,0,0,0,,I want to be a rainbow that reaches out to hope
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.90,0:01:46.88,Lucy-Ep-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,306.667)\fade(370,270)}Ep. 44 - Little! Little!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.35,0:02:03.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.41,0:02:12.29,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The moon is out.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.59,0:02:34.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is that Kate's dress?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.50,0:02:35.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.71,0:02:36.51,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy's?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.23,0:02:40.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. A button came off it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.39,0:02:44.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lovely dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.80,0:02:47.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's getting a little tight for her, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.26,0:02:49.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She probably couldn't wear it in the coming year...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.23,0:02:58.68,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Moon, you know where Lucy is, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.68,0:03:00.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.09,0:03:17.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, why won't you go to sleep already?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.17,0:03:20.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sleepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.71,0:03:22.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.05,0:03:26.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How else can we go about looking for Lucy?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.80,0:03:30.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Worried about Lucy who wouldn't come home,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.70,0:03:34.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,we all grew completely unable to get any sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.89,0:03:40.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy, where are you?
Comment: 0,0:04:34.33,0:04:36.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.76,0:04:52.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, you can even swim underwater?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.71,0:05:05.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Stop, Prospero!\NYou're tickling me! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.92,0:05:20.75,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Prospero, so you were actually a dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.80,0:05:27.81,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just a dream, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.71,0:05:35.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You had a dream, Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.27,0:05:38.94,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was chasing after a girl I felt like I know very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.94,0:05:41.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But when I caught up to her,\Nshe didn't have a face.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.73,0:05:43.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, how uncanny.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.12,0:05:45.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure I know that girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.28,0:05:49.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I felt like I was about to call her by the name\Nback when I was chasing her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.54,0:05:50.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Was that the only thing you saw?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.63,0:05:53.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, it continued after that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.49,0:05:56.54,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did you meet some more people that you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.91,0:06:01.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I dreamt that I was drowning in the pond\Nand crying for help, but nobody came to help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.42,0:06:05.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,None of the people standing on the shore\Neven turned to look at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.10,0:06:06.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My, poor thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.55,0:06:08.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a dream, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.63,0:06:12.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Still, having nobody to come save you...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.35,0:06:15.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think I lost my voice back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.70,0:06:19.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There, see? A common happening in any dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.31,0:06:24.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, weren't there any clues in your dream that could help you remember your past?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.52,0:06:27.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The cat turned into a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.82,0:06:28.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.34,0:06:30.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Prospero...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.91,0:06:36.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. What happened is you turned into a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.30,0:06:41.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Cat turned into a dog, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.80,0:06:44.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it didn't bring back any particular memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.44,0:06:48.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if I used to keep that dog as a pet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.90,0:06:49.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.90,0:06:53.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Since you love animals,\Nyou'd be likely to keep a dog too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.64,0:06:57.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let's call it enough of talking about dreams, Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.06,0:07:01.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Today we'll be coming with a visit\Nto the Duchess of York, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.91,0:07:04.08,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. But I...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.08,0:07:06.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The Duchess is a very amiable lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.71,0:07:09.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,After hearing your story,\Nshe'd become very sympathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.70,0:07:11.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,She's dying to hear more about yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.82,0:07:13.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I have nothing to tell about myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.74,0:07:18.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I only remember things that happened\Nafter my arrival to this house. Before that - nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.71,0:07:21.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.12,0:07:25.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure the Duchess would be contented\Nwith just being able to meet you, Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.00,0:07:36.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I was never particularly religious.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.71,0:07:42.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But that Sunday, I prayed to God earnestly\Nthat we find Lucy soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.49,0:07:47.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Honey, are you going to look for Lucy today as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.10,0:07:51.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's no telling if we'd ever find her\Nif we just keep walking around haphazardly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.13,0:07:53.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's still better than doing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.66,0:07:55.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.13,0:07:57.05,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Father, let's go look for her either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.05,0:07:58.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.81,0:08:03.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When that notice in Adelaide Times is published,\Nsomeone might try to reach out to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.42,0:08:09.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But there's no newspaper on Sunday,\Nso we might as well go walk around again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.44,0:08:10.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.11,0:08:11.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.48,0:08:15.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need for you to come too.\NI'd rather you help me with housework.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.49,0:08:18.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Even Little must now be searching for her somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.83,0:08:47.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! It's Little!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.25,0:08:52.20,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It really did look like Little.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.20,0:08:55.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He must've come home to see if Lucy returned or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.99,0:08:57.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What a smart dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.85,0:08:59.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,He's not a dog, but a dingo.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.48,0:09:25.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed, this dress looks\Nvery becoming on you, Little Miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.81,0:09:29.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I almost feel like I'm a queen herself!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.38,0:09:39.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,If you become the Little Miss of the Princeton family,\Nyou will actually be as happy as the queen herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.35,0:09:42.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm not the daughter of this family.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.22,0:09:48.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,With my hand on my heart, the madam does seem\Nto think of you as of her real child.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.99,0:09:54.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,As evident by her naming you Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.42,0:09:59.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Emily was the madam's daughter,\Nwho died when she was just two.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.14,0:10:00.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know that, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.89,0:10:05.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,And when you call her mother,\Nshe literally starts beaming with happiness!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.29,0:10:09.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I have another mother out there somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.04,0:10:16.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I don't think you'll find a mother as kind and beautiful as our madam anywhere else in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.50,0:10:21.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can't remember anything about you past, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.55,0:10:27.06,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Just leave things as they are now and strap in\Nfor a life of happiness as the new Emily in this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.91,0:10:31.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not supposed to be bearing this name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.40,0:10:39.99,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You look gorgeous, Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.45,0:10:43.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That dress looks great on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:45.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.49,0:10:48.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,The Duchess is waiting for us.\NLet's set out now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.80,0:11:04.19,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We're approaching the Adelaide Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.19,0:11:06.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's where I was hit by a carriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.70,0:11:07.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.97,0:11:44.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Here is the mansion of the Duke of York, acting\Nas an emissary of Her Majesty in Southern Australia.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.15,0:11:45.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder it's so magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.98,0:11:51.64,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But it's unthinkable that Lucy\Nwould come anywhere near this part of the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.64,0:11:52.90,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.29,0:12:15.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's only been three days\Nsince she's lost her memory?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.59,0:12:16.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.79,0:12:19.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it rightly curious?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.17,0:12:25.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You're probably feeling befuddled,\Nnot even knowing who might you be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.29,0:12:26.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, very much so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.78,0:12:28.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.09,0:12:32.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When grown-ups don't know who they are,\Nthey simply cannot stop worrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.83,0:12:36.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But you're handling it remarkably well,\Neven though you're still so small.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.74,0:12:39.03,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's thanks to my mother's kind support.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.65,0:12:40.98,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mother's?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.98,0:12:43.74,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I asked her to call me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.74,0:12:47.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I've also come to think of her as of my own child.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.30,0:12:50.71,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I know you've been yearning to have a child\Nsince long ago, Sylvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.71,0:12:51.57,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.21,0:12:56.17,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'm sure those three days\Nwere the happiest time of your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.17,0:12:57.67,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Very much so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.29,0:13:03.52,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,My wife is getting unreasonably obsessed with this child,\Neven making me ever so slightly worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.52,0:13:04.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.79,0:13:07.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Her memory should return one of these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.84,0:13:11.78,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sylvia, the very moment that happens,\Nyour newly acquired motherhood will be over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.78,0:13:12.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.44,0:13:18.42,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, I've arranged for a notice regarding this child\Nto be posted in tomorrow's Monday newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.42,0:13:23.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, upon seeing that notice,\Nher real parents would make themselves known.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.07,0:13:27.45,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm sure Emily would never forget you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.44,0:13:29.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Emily?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.03,0:13:31.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Most certainly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.13,0:13:42.25,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's remarkable how compassionate the Duchess is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.25,0:13:42.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.88,0:13:50.30,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, dear, I'd like to stop by at a shoemaker's.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.30,0:13:52.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you want to buy shoes for yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.11,0:13:53.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, for Emily!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.82,0:13:58.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I found a good pair the other day, but I didn't like\Nthe ribbon on them so I ordered it replaced.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.66,0:14:02.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,When I saw those shoes, I knew at once\Nthey'd fit perfectly with this dress.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.23,0:14:06.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Max. Stop at the shoemaker's shop\Non King William Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.45,0:14:16.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Those shoes would fit perfectly\Nwith your wedding gown.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.21,0:14:18.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. But they're so expensive!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.93,0:14:20.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.10,0:14:22.40,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't possibly afford them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.80,0:14:26.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be working harder than ever\Nand before long, we'll buy them!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.22,0:14:28.96,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Such expensive shoes are a money thrown away!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.96,0:14:29.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.18,0:14:32.15,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But before that comes Lucy-May.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.15,0:14:34.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right. Gotta find Lucy first.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.62,0:14:58.33,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So? They're not too tight?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.33,0:14:59.37,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.37,0:15:02.85,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Those are wonderfully cute shoes!\NAnd they fit the dress perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.17,0:15:09.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You can go home in those shoes, Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.18,0:15:17.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, Emily, is there anything else you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.92,0:15:19.47,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.47,0:15:21.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need to be shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.52,0:15:23.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.90,0:15:24.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.69,0:15:27.36,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'd like to stop the carriage for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.73,0:15:31.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Where? We can stop at whatever shop you'd like.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.26,0:15:35.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that. I just thought\Nwe'll be approaching Adelaide Bridge soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.73,0:15:36.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.70,0:15:38.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to stop at the bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.43,0:15:39.38,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.38,0:15:42.88,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I want to inspect once more this spot where I was lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.54,0:15:45.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean you remembered something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.17,0:15:48.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I don't remember anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.61,0:15:50.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I want to walk over bridge again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.91,0:15:55.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. We'll stop the carriage\Nat the Adelaide Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.37,0:16:20.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think she remembered something?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.76,0:16:23.09,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, I didn't get that kind of impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.30,0:16:38.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How is it? Anything comes to your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.37,0:16:43.61,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.45,0:16:55.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing... I remember nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.22,0:17:07.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you can't help it with crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.00,0:17:11.13,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.\NYou'll definitely regain your memory one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.13,0:17:12.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go home for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.10,0:17:17.31,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I'll return to the carriage soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.31,0:17:20.04,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Can you please let me stay here for a little longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.04,0:17:22.87,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. I don't see why I shouldn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.51,0:17:38.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.12,0:17:42.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Only what she just said -\Ngive her some time alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.20,0:18:13.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dear, it charges at Emily.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.21,0:18:13.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.04,0:18:26.46,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dear, Emily needs help...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.46,0:18:28.50,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No. Wait a moment, Sylvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.96,0:18:31.24,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it already!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.86,0:18:35.55,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I said stop! You're tickling me, Little!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.21,0:18:37.14,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.55,0:18:42.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.10,0:18:48.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.08,0:19:06.27,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Little!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.15,0:19:10.83,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little! Little! So it was you, Little!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.10,0:19:17.84,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I think Emily is no more, Sylvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.84,0:19:19.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.35,0:19:36.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom, I'm hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.61,0:19:38.34,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you know, Tob?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.34,0:19:41.56,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We'll have dinner once your dad and brother are back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.56,0:19:43.43,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if they'll bring Lucy along.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.19,0:19:46.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's Little!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.44,0:19:48.79,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! That was Little's barking!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.46,0:19:51.92,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did he find her?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.50,0:19:55.82,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.82,0:19:58.00,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find Lucy? Tell me, Little!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.91,0:20:04.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.23,0:20:17.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom.
Comment: 0,0:20:21.24,0:20:21.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.73,0:20:24.39,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.85,0:20:28.10,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy! It really is you, Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.09,0:20:40.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, is that a carriage parked in front of our house?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.16,0:20:42.49,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.84,0:20:47.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder who came in it.\NThat's a pretty extravagant carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.72,0:20:52.01,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Little is here...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.01,0:20:52.97,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That means...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.97,0:20:55.63,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's it! Lucy had returned!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.20,0:21:07.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but we'll have to leave soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.59,0:21:08.48,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.91,0:21:11.72,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stress it enough\Nhow grateful we are for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.12,0:21:15.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,No, we only did what anyone would've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.35,0:21:20.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, but I hope I'll get a chance to discuss things\Nmore thoroughly with you one of these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.65,0:21:21.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.18,0:21:25.80,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You came to Southern Australia\Naiming to build a new farm, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.80,0:21:27.32,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.32,0:21:29.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Lucy explained everything to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.02,0:21:32.44,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,I also operate several farms and ranches.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.44,0:21:35.66,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,So I'd love to hear all about it next time we meet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.66,0:21:36.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.50,0:21:44.18,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Let us go, Sylvia.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.24,0:21:52.35,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Emily...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.42,0:22:06.62,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.81,0:22:24.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why I've been so worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.73,0:22:28.12,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,You came to love that child deeply, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.20,0:22:41.53,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Right! You need to sit still, Little. Like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.01,0:22:43.95,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.95,0:22:47.77,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me in more about Mr. Princeton's mansion.\NI want details!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.77,0:22:52.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How many bedrooms does it have?\NEight? Nine? Maybe all ten?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.02,0:22:56.22,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,They had a room filled right up to the top with books.\NAh! You can't move yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.22,0:22:58.73,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,It's your fault for gathering so much dirt!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.73,0:23:01.28,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Where in the world have you been rambling\Nwhile I was away?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.71,0:23:03.02,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,How about food?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.02,0:23:05.41,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, was it good?\NWhat kind of dishes did they serve?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.41,0:23:06.69,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All kinds!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.69,0:23:08.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"All kinds" means nothing to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.60,0:23:12.26,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,That's because all the food they served\Nwas something I never tried before.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.26,0:23:13.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But everything was delicious!
Comment: 0,0:23:13.58,0:23:14.58,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.00,0:23:17.65,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! You can't go, Little!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.80,0:23:20.91,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Stop, Little!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.91,0:23:22.21,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lucy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.21,0:23:24.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of stuff did they have for the tea break?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.93,0:23:27.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Stop I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.69,0:23:29.93,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What snacks did they have?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.34,0:23:31.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,All sorts of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.74,0:23:34.60,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,"All sorts" means nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.00,0:23:41.70,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Biscuits with raisins, soft and delicate muffins,\Npancakes fully covered in honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.70,0:23:46.11,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Sweet fresh cream and spongecake\Nwith strawberry jam in-between!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.44,0:23:50.76,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Also some of the best chocolate ever,\Nsent directly from France!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.19,0:24:06.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,We found a wallaby,\Nwhich is like a kangaroo, and is very cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.59,0:24:10.89,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,But while we chased the wallaby,\NTob suddenly disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.89,0:24:14.59,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Next on Lucy-May of the Southern Rainbow:\N"Tob Disappeared".
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.59,0:24:16.07,Lucy-Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
